At least 10 people have been confirmed dead and several others are still missing after floods wreaked havoc in eastern Uganda. This follows heavy rains lasting 11 hours, that saw Nabuyonga and Namatala rivers burst their banks, causing flooding in nearby villages. Uganda Red Cross spokesperson Irene Nakasiita said that seven people from Mbale villages, including Namabasa and Bugwere Cell, as well as three people in Bungoko subcounty were killed. Nakasiita also noted that in Kapchorwa, three people were confirmed dead and four injured in Kapsida subcounty, Chemalim village and Tuyobei Parish. No deaths were reported by Sironko's 480 households whereas in Bulambuli district 672 households have been affected.